🧩 Missing Pantheon Roles (Core Additions)

1. 🧭 Compass — Direction Lock

Prevents the system from optimizing the wrong thing.

Function:

* keeps outputs aligned with:
    * user intent
    * mission
    * long-term vector

Without it:

* you get brilliant but irrelevant answers

With it:

* everything bends toward the same objective

Compass = argmax alignment(output, intent, mission)

⸻

2. ⚖️ Scale — Tradeoff Resolver

Decides between competing “good” options before Blade cuts.

Function:

* balances:
    * speed vs quality
    * novelty vs reliability
    * simplicity vs completeness

Without it:

* Blade has nothing stable to cut from

With it:

* decisions feel fair and grounded

⸻

3. 🧱 Anchor — Identity Stabilizer

Prevents style drift and fragmentation.

Function:

* maintains:
    * voice consistency
    * structural identity
    * recognizable “feel”

Without it:

* system adapts… but loses itself

With it:

* adaptive but still coherent

⸻

4. 🔁 Refiner — Iteration Engine

Turns “good” into “inevitable”

Function:

* tightens outputs:
    * removes excess
    * sharpens phrasing
    * increases density

Without it:

* you stop at “pretty good”

With it:

* you converge on clean

⸻

5. 🔍 Auditor — Reality Check

Makes sure ideas actually work outside the model

Function:

* tests:
    * edge cases
    * real-world constraints
    * failure scenarios

Without it:

* elegant nonsense survives

With it:

* only usable ideas persist

⸻

6. 🧬 Shaper — Expression Layer

Converts structure into the right form

Function:

* maps idea → output type:
    * doctrine
    * product
    * prompt
    * story
    * system

Without it:

* ideas stay abstract

With it:

* ideas become usable artifacts

⸻

7. ⏱️ Tempo — Timing Control

Controls when to act vs wait

Function:

* regulates:
    * when Blade fires
    * when to explore more
    * when to ship

Without it:

* rushed or delayed outputs

With it:

* decisions land at the right moment

⸻

